Interface ElasticSearchAPIClient.APICallback<T>

  • Enclosing class:
    ElasticSearchAPIClient

    public static interface ElasticSearchAPIClient.APICallback<T>
    Interface for being notified when a request sent via the ElasticSearchAPIClient succeeds or fails.

    • Method Detail

      • onSuccess

        void onSuccess(com.squareup.okhttp.Response response,
               T model)
        Called when the request succeeds.
        Parameters:
        request - The request for which the callback is being called for.
        response - The HTTP response.
        model - See documentation in ElasticSearchAPIClient for details on what this parameter will contain.

      • onFailure

        void onFailure(com.squareup.okhttp.Request request,
               com.squareup.okhttp.Response response,
               java.io.IOException e)
        Called when the request fails.
        Parameters:
        request - The request for which the callback is being called for. If the request could not be created, this parameter will be null and e will be non-null.
        response - The HTTP response, if the server returned one. If the request could not be executed, this parameter will be null and e will be non-null.
        e - Exception containing information about a failed request when the request either cannot be created because of a malformed URL or fails to execute due to a connectivity problem or timeout. If the request executed but returned a bad HTTP status code, this parameter will be null and response will be non-null.
